<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Thomson, John. Journal, Mackenzie River, 1800-1802. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0021</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p style="text-align:justify;">to hunt Hares &#8211; sent him off immediately to the other side to set his Snares<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  N.B. all this last Band of Indians are cloathed with Beaver skins, &amp; several of them have Robes<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> indeed the greatest part of the Indians that I have seen here are cloathed in Beaver<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Saturday the 20<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Fine Mild Weather<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The young Lad came back from the other side<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> he brought all his Snares, as he says he is unwell consequently wanted to go away<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  My 2 hunters arrived, they brought 42 hares, one of them is an old Lazy Rascal, &amp; has never made a single skin, altho he has been hunting here since the 24<sup>th</sup> ultim<sup>o</sup> he has taken to this date only 73 hares<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Sunday the 21<sup>st</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Fine Weather<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sent the y Men back to their Snares<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Monday the 22<sup>d</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  In the morning 2 young Men arrived from the Grand Lac below &#8211; gave them Drams &amp;<sup>c</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  They paid 29 Skins Credits &amp; Traded 1½ skins, 1 orig<sup>l</sup> skin, 2 carribou collets &amp; 10 Skins worth of Dried &amp; Pounded Meat<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Tuesday the 23<sup>d</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The Indians arrived yesterday went away, one of them took 6 Skins on Credit<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> the other owes a balance of 26 skins<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Wednesday the 24<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  In the evening 2 of the hunters arrived from behind<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> they brought 57 hares &#8211; a little after the young Lad from the other side arrived<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> he brought 51 hares<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">25<sup>th</sup> Christmas day<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sent the Hunters back to their Snares &#8211; gave Plante a good Dram &amp; the Prie of Meat<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Friday the 26<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The young Lad from the other side arrived<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> the Blockhead brought 26 hares &amp; all the Snares but told him that he must for his pains go back again &amp; set them in the same place<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Saturday the 27<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The young Lad after Dark yesterday evening Deserted &#8211; the Rogue was cunning enough to demand the payment yesterday of his hares<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  In the evening the 2 hunters brought 64 hares<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Sunday the 28<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The young Man that left this the 18<sup>th</sup> Ins<sup>t</sup> to go for his orignal arrived this morning along with 2 others, gave</p>
